docs/help-in-depth.md
     1вҶ’# Help in Depth
     3вҶ’The built-in help is formatted using the Help class.
     4вҶ’You can configure the Help behaviour by modifying data properties and methods using `.configureHelp()`, or by subclassing using `.createHelp()` if you prefer.
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’Example file: [configure-help.js](../examples/configure-help.js)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    20вҶ’## Data Properties
    22вҶ’The data properties are:
    23вҶ’
    24вҶ’- `helpWidth`: specify the wrap width, useful for unit tests
    25вҶ’- `minWidthToWrap`: specify required width to allow wrapping (default 40)
    26вҶ’- `showGlobalOptions`: show a section with the global options from the parent command(s)
    27вҶ’- `sortSubcommands`: sort the subcommands alphabetically
    28вҶ’- `sortOptions`: sort the options alphabetically
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’Example files:
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    34вҶ’## Stringify and Style
    36вҶ’The `Help` object has narrowly focused methods to allow customising the displayed help.
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’The stringify routines take an object (`Command` or `Option` or `Argument`) and produce a string. For example you could change the way subcommands are listed:
    39вҶ’
    40вҶ’```js
    41вҶ’program.configureHelp({
    42вҶ’  subcommandTerm: (cmd) => cmd.name() // just show the name instead of usage
    43вҶ’});
    44вҶ’```
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   118вҶ’## Layout
   120вҶ’Utility methods which control the layout include `padWidth`, `boxWrap`, and `formatItem`. These can be overridden to change the layout or replace with an alternative implementation.
   121вҶ’
   122вҶ’Example files:
   123вҶ’
   124вҶ’- `formatItem`: [help-centered.mjs](../examples/help-centered.mjs)
   125вҶ’- `formatItem`: [man-style-help.mjs](../examples/man-style-help.mjs)
   126вҶ’- `boxwrap`: [color-help-replacement.mjs](../examples/color-help-replacement.mjs)
   127вҶ’
docs/options-in-depth.md
     2вҶ’# Options in Depth
     4вҶ’The README covers declaring and using options, and mostly parsing will work the way you and your users expect. This page covers some special cases
     5вҶ’and subtle issues in depth.
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’- [Options taking varying numbers of option-arguments](#options-taking-varying-numbers-of-option-arguments)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    15вҶ’## Options taking varying numbers of option-arguments
    17вҶ’Certain options take a varying number of arguments:
    18вҶ’
    19вҶ’```js
    20вҶ’program
    21вҶ’   .option('-c, --compress [percentage]') // 0 or 1
    22вҶ’   .option('--preprocess <file...>') // 1 or more
    23вҶ’   .option('--test [name...]') // 0 or more
    24вҶ’```
    25вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    30вҶ’### Parsing ambiguity вҖҰ
    79вҶ’#### Alternative: Make `--` part of your syntax
    81вҶ’Rather than trying to teach your users what `--` does, you could just make it part of your syntax.
    82вҶ’
    83вҶ’```js
    84вҶ’program.usage('[options] -- [technique]');
    85вҶ’```
    86вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   104вҶ’#### Alternative: Put options last
   106вҶ’Commander follows the GNU convention for parsing and allows options before or after the command-arguments, or intermingled.
   107вҶ’So by putting the options last, the command-arguments do not get confused with the option-arguments.
   108вҶ’
   109вҶ’```js
   110вҶ’program.usage('[technique] [options]');
   111вҶ’```
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   126вҶ’#### Alternative: Use options instead of command-arguments
   128вҶ’This is a bit more radical, but completely avoids the parsing ambiguity!
   129вҶ’
   130вҶ’```js
   131вҶ’program
   132вҶ’  .name('cook')
   133вҶ’  .option('-t, --technique <technique>', 'cooking technique')
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   148вҶ’## Combining short options, and options taking arguments
   150вҶ’Multiple boolean short options can be combined after a single `-`, like `ls -al`. You can also include just
   151вҶ’a single short option which might take a value, as any following characters will
   152вҶ’be taken as the value.
   153вҶ’
   154вҶ’This means that by default you can not combine short options which may take an argument.
   155вҶ’
   156вҶ’```js
   157вҶ’program
   158вҶ’  .name('collect')
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   191вҶ’### Combining short options as if boolean вҖҰ
docs/parsing-and-hooks.md
     1вҶ’# Parsing life cycle and hooks
     3вҶ’The processing starts with an array of args. Each command processes and removes the options it understands, and passes the remaining args to the next subcommand.
     4вҶ’The final command calls the action handler.
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’Starting with top-level command (program):
